Wuhan is a place that is neither north nor south, so they will have the brute strength of northerners and the shrewdness of southerners. Like to live small. And Love Wuhan Love to say, a lot of Wuhan people, is not allow anyone to say that Wuhan is not good.

By Kong Bingxin

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Famous writer Fang Fang

Some of the Chinese, who have been locked up for the Lunar New Year since Feb. 3 because of a new outbreak of pneumonia, have begun to resume work as needed.

In a tweet that day, fang Fang, a famous writer who grew up in Wuhan, wrote: "On the Tenth Day of the Lunar New Year, another sunny day. Yesterday I thought it would continue to rain, but today it suddenly turned out fine. People seeking medical treatment may feel a little warmer because of the sunshine. "

She to a friend in the front-line doctor to understand the situation, the other side took time to tell: First, Wuhan medical supplies in a "tight balance" state, the situation is grim, can not be taken lightly. 2. The grass-roots government, community and village isolation measures are effective, but we still hope that people from all walks of life will show more concern and provide assistance to grass-roots hospitals. (C) handling of suspected cases should be more appropriate and should not be handed over to the community for a long period of time. 4. All hospitals are busy and the number of confirmed and suspected patients is increasing. 5. The epidemic situation can only be controlled if all the people in the hospital are in the hospital and all the people in the hospital are isolated.

How hard it is to mourn the people's livelihood. Fang Fang said, in the face of those who struggle, die, tears, we are not easy, he also felt very helpless, but then thought, in addition to cheer up, what else? We have to carry on, at the same time, in the spare time to take care of others, to help carry on, in any case, always insist.

Fortunately, the good news is on its way to Foshan, Mount Thor Hospital, where patients are beginning to be admitted; there are figures showing that the number of patients in the provinces seems to have decreased, the cure rate is high, and the mortality rate is low... in an interview with the Xinmin Weekly, Fang Fang said, wuhan people are actually honest people, listen to the government, they love the city, love to say: "Now, my wish is, sick people, have a hospital to go. I pray for them. ".

Xinmin Weekly:

The first is one of the most basic and understated questions. Are there enough supplies in Wuhan since the city was sealed off? Do you have enough face masks, disinfectants, commonly used medicines, etc. ? Is Your daily life ok? Like shopping for vegetables and so on

Fang Fang

Everyday things can still be guaranteed. The price of vegetables has risen slightly, but not by much. But I think it's GONNA go up. After all, the cold and New Year, but also at the risk of infection, the rise point should be. No one's complaining about it. You can't buy a mask, it's in high demand, and it's used up. It's just that if you stay home, you don't get much use out of it. I've only used two so far, and the third is still in use. I didn't notice the disinfectant, and I figured if no one else was in the house, it would be the same as usual. So, not paying attention. The pharmacy had not been open for a while, and now asked to open, but did not know how the situation.

Do you think we can make "isolation" more humane?

Of course. For example, there are hotels near the hospital, there are no guests for the New Year, Charter a hotel, let the suspicious patients isolated there, organize a medical team to patrol the hotel, many of the mild infection, do not have to run around, so as to infect others. This is much easier and quicker than building a hospital on the spur of the moment (and it can be built at the same time, without conflict) . This suggestion seems to have been put forward a long time ago, but no one has listened to it. Of course, I may have other ideas, but I'm a layman and I don't know. In short, as long as one person in the family is sick, once does not go to the hospital, the situation is still very miserable. Some light ones, because of this, may get heavier and even die.

This unusual Spring Festival, Wuhan People Have Become "Xianfeng Emperor" (crazy) . What do you mainly do at home? As far as you know, other Wuhan friends around and what are the stories of joy in pain?

I'm like daily. Must have slept in the morning. One more thing to do with my twitter account. Then get a dog, Cook for your daughter, and everyone asks how it's going. Once in a while I go on the treadmill for an hour. I used to run for an hour a day, but I've run less recently.

You are advised to write "the story of the walled city" . Will you consider writing a book on the subject in the future?

Not at the moment.

In general, Wuhan People "do not believe in evil" , do not accept the appointment; you "million Arrow through the heart" , I grow proudly. In this epidemic, at the beginning of a dinner party activities, there are running around, but later, the vast majority of Wuhan people still hold their ground, reflecting the city's sense of responsibility. What do you think of the strength of the Wuhan People?

The people of Wuhan are actually quite honest. Although there is a careless dilettante of Jin, dare to say dare to dare to fight, have the spirit of the rivers and lakes, also Zhangyi. But he's honest at heart. He's not too brave. There is no doubt that they listen to the government. And Love Wuhan Love to say, a lot of Wuhan people, is not allow anyone to say that Wuhan is not good. They're gonNA kick your ass. And Fun. Wuhan is a place that is neither north nor south, so they will have the brute strength of northerners and the shrewdness of southerners. Like to live small. The closure of the city was probably the biggest event in Wuhan's history since the Revolution of 1911.
